ECB’s Wellink Says Trichet Would Be ‘Fantastic Candidate’ to Be IMF Leader

-- B y   J u r j e n   v a n   d e   P o l
-- 
2011-05-19T05:09:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/ecb-s-wellink-says-trichet-would-be-fantastic-candidate-to-be-imf-leader.html
European Central Bank Governing
Council member Nout Wellink said the bank’s president Jean-
Claude Trichet could succeed  Dominique Strauss-Kahn  at the
 International Monetary Fund .   “I know a fantastic candidate, that’s  Jean-Claude Trichet 
of the ECB,” Wellink, who also heads the Dutch central bank,
told the Dutch talk show Knevel & Van den Brink late last night.
“If he leaves there he can go to  Washington , as successor to
Strauss-Kahn.”   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jurjen van de Pol at 
 jvandepol@bloomberg.net  